Boil a large #pot{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} for your pasta. Very finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{4}. Cut open the skin of the @pork sausages{1} and remove the meat.

Chop the very top and bottom from the @courgette{4} and slice in half lengthways. Slice each half lengthways into 5 more strips and then chop widthways into 1cm cubes. Peel and very finely chop the @garlic clove{2}.

Place the @walnuts{2} in a clean #tea towel{} and whack them gently with a #saucepan{} to break them up.

Heat @olive oil{3%tsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the sausage meat and break it up with a #spoon{}. Cook for ~{4-5%minutes} until cooked then remove and keep to the side.

Cook your @fettuccine{400} in the boiling water until 'al dente'.

> 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a hint of firmness left in the middle.

Before you drain the pasta make sure you keep @pasta water{1%cup}. This will help you create a silky sauce.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a frying pan on medium heat. Once hot add the courgettes and garlic and cook for ~{5%minutes}. Meanwhile finely chop the @olives{2}. Add in the walnuts and olives and cook for ~{1%minute} before moving to the next step.

Grate in the zest of @lemon{1/2}(zested) and pour in @pasta water{1%cup}. As it begins to bubble tip in your pasta, the sausage meat and the @parmesan cheese{4}(grated). Toss everything together and at the last minute add the parsley and @lemon juice{3%tsp} before serving.